leetcode 283 move zeroes:
Given an integer array nums, move all 0's to the end of it while maintaining the relative order of the non-zero elements.
Note that you must do this in-place without making a copy of the array.
Example 1:
Input: nums = [0,1,0,3,12]
Output: [1,3,12,0,0]

Example 2:
Input: nums = [0]
Output: [0]
INTIUTION:
1.it is certain that all the non zero numbers should be it the front of the array(vector).
NOTE:it should not change the order of the array
2.remaining place upto the size of the array must be zero.
APPROACH:
1.create a pointer i=0.
2.using for loop,traverse through the list 
3.if while traversing the array ,the element is zero,set nums[i]=that element .
4.increment the i pointer.
5.after traversing all the elements in array ,the i will be one value that is,if i=5 it means,upto 4 there are non zero elements .
6.from i,to size(array)-1 set all to zero.
CODE:
class Solution {
public:
    void moveZeroes(vector<int>& nums) {
        int j=0;
        for(int i=0;i<nums.size();i++){
            if(nums[i]!=0){
                nums[j]=nums[i];
                j++;
            }
        }
        for(int k=j;k<nums.size();k++){
            nums[k]=0;
        }
    }
};
